reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 21, 2022
reviews.reviewText: The assembly on this was easy, it is lightweight and yet built to last. Love that the back slides into slots instead of those stupid little nails that always end up pulling out…this won’t happen with these shelves!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 1, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars DEFECTIVE DO NOT BUY
reviews.reviewText: Two of the panels, meant for the top and bottom, have about a 1/2 inch extra on the length compared to the other panels which are cut correctly. So short of finding a power saw to chop off the excess and make new holes there is no way to actually build and use this.Even worse, the “product support” is useless.MoniBloom has the worst customer service I’ve ever dealt with. As the manufacturer, they’re supposed to be able to send replacement pieces for defective products.The person I emailed only replied “amazon fulfilled it talk to them” so I sent them a picture of the product support page that made it clear they were responsible for replacing it only for them to repeat the same thing and ignore my next three emails.Kept badgering them and apparently the replacement parts I need are out of stock and they don’t know when/if they’ll get them back in.Waste of money, do not buy monibloom productsP.S. it should be noted that amazon customer service was helpful but I missed the full refund window (having assumed it wouldn’t be defective and I could build it later) and they can’t do anything about replacing the defective pieces.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 11, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars I purchased this item specifically for its size
reviews.reviewText: This shelf unit was exactly what I needed in a specific space in my apartment, and it serves primarily as a bookshelf there. The unit is lightweight, but seems sturdy enough, I guess. The shelves are constructed in such a way that there is a frame/ridge around each edge of each shelf, causing books to run into a tiny "curb" instead of sitting flush against the side of the cubby. Removing and flipping the shelf makes no difference. I suppose it isn't a huge deal, and it's not worth returning the unit. But, if purchasers plan on using this as a bookshelf, heads-up.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 27, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Fits my small space
reviews.reviewText: I’ve struggled to find a place for some books in my tiny she cave. It was easy to assemble but I wouldn’t test the weight limits for the shelves. I like that it’s real wood even tho it’s quite thin. Looks good.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 2, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Well made small shelf unit
reviews.reviewText: Nice, well made unit. Bamboo shelves and sides are thin. I would not put too much weight on them but it is did.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 21, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Parts do not fit, quality control issue
reviews.reviewText: I tried twice to get a usable unit. The mounting holes for the top and bottom panels do not match up with the side panels If the groove for the back panel is lined up, the forward mounting holes do not. I design machines for a living and a simple CAD layout would show the error. This is a serious Quality control issue. The fact that they let this design out of the factory without actually trying to assemble one says quite a bit about the manufacturer. I was looking forward to having and using this product. It would have served my purposes well. Unfortunately, I have to find another one or take the time to build my own.
